reviews.review_text:
When I paint my Masterpiece.. This recording captures the band riding high into N.Y.C which was one of the few places in the world that could absorb the circus and not be fazed one little bit.
This is high energy throughout.
A first set that increases in intensity
By the time they hit Louie, Louie
it is a splashdown puddle.
I was at this show but it  is very hazy at this late date. Pretty sure this was the night I ran down the emergency exit steps in the middle of Morning Dew and a brother says to me on the 8th avenue pavement, “Are they done?”
Just smiled, “Probably not but I am”
86 was the coma, 87 was Dylan
88 was Brent shifting gears
and 89-90 was high cotton.
Bigger than The Beatles
High Cotton
This Second Set contains only one ballad
Which followed a rowdy Bertha-) Cumberland and LLR melts into a stellar Terrapin
and you be hard pressed to get 
A better post space with
Trucking-)GDTRFB-) Morning Dew
Bigger than a drive-in movie
For sure 👍
